Nearly 170,000 Central Maine Power Co. customers were still without electricity Friday night in the wake of a strong spring storm, and the utility company warned that it could be two days before power is fully restored.
CMP reported 169,132 customers still without power as of 12:20 a.m. Saturday, down from a peak of more than 204,000 earlier in the day.
The outages reported by CMP were spread across 14 counties, with Lincoln, Kennebec, Somerset and Waldo reporting the most customers without power.
Emera Maine, which provides electricity to northern and eastern Maine, reported 64,302 outages at 9:30 a.m. Friday.
“With heavy, wet snow causing dangerous driving conditions and power outages, I am closing state government offices,” Mills said in a statement.